article.headline: Kent St. 76, Buffalo 66
article.story: AMHERST, N.Y. (AP) -- Al Fisher scored 20 points as Kent State defeated Buffalo 76-66 in Mid-American Conference action Tuesday night. Already leading 22-14, Kent State (22-5, 11-2 MAC) took command of the game midway through the first half with a 13-2 run. Fisher and Haminn Quaintance had back-to-back dunks during the nine-minute mark of the half. A 3-pointer by Mike Scott with 6:16 left in the half capped the run and gave the Golden Flashes a 34-16 lead. Buffalo (8-17, 2-11 MAC) was held without a field goal for over seven minutes during the game's decisive first half. The Bulls pulled to within eight with 2:40 left in the second half following an acrobatic scoop shot by Byron Mulkey that capped a quick 8-0 run but came no closer. Quaintance finished with 14 points for Kent State, winners of five straight games and eight of nine. Scott added 13. The Bulls, who have lost three straight and 12 of their last 14, were led by Andy Robinson with 17 points. Calvin Betts added 11 points and 11 rebounds. The game marked Kent State's 1000th win in program history.
